Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unplaceAllGuides(25.10)                                unplaceAllGuides(25.10)

Name
       unplaceAllGuides - Clears all constraints (guides, regions, and fences)
       from the floorplan

Syntax
       unplaceAllGuides

       [-help]

       Clears  all  constraints  (guides, regions, and fences) from the floor-
       plan. You can use this command after importing the design.

       Note: The unplaceAllGuides command does not delete instGroups.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the unplaceAllGuides command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man unplaceAllGuides

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

